<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021497FEC4FEBFFE06" bold="true" box="[199,345,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA160215F8FEC4FDE5FE06" box="[424,515,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,356,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-112@2.[151,1436,345,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. H. (H.) ferreri sp. nov., female; B. H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., male; C. Same, female; D. H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., male; E. Same, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598175/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA1602165FFEC4FDBFFE06" box="[527,601,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">3A–H</figureCitation>
): Body long oval, convex, dark brown, dorsal surface dull-shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FE38FAB9FD7E" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Head (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021542FE38FE8CFE22" box="[274,362,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) transverse, widest across compound eyes. Vertex finely covered with small punctures and each puncture bearing a short, thin seta. Genae and epistoma covered with denser punctures and setae relative to punctures and setae on vertex. Labrum reddish brown, narrower than epistoma, covered in apical portion with bristles of medium length. Antennal tubercles weakly prominent, antenna (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA160217DDFE54FC05FD96" box="[909,995,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) longer than head plus pronotum, club composed of four apical antennomeres. Relative lengths of antennomeres: 0.46: 0.23: 0.76: 0.72: 0.74: 0.73: 0.70: 0.63: 0.53: 0.51:0.65; relative widths of antennomeres: 0.29: 0.24: 0.26: 0.28: 0.27: 0.30: 0.31: 0.36: 0.35: 0.35: 0.42. Antennomere I slightly expanded; antennomere II shortest, about as long as wide; antennomere III longest, more than twice as long as antennomere II, antennomeres IV–VI similar, shorter than antennomere III, antennomere VII distinctly expanded near apex, antennomere VIII about twice as long as wide, distinctly expanded near apex, antennomeres IX–X similar, longer than wide and expanded near apices, antennomere XI with apex rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FD57FF1DFC2A" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021517FD50FE47FC9A" box="[327,417,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) about as long as wide, widest at middle; dorsal surface covered with dense small punctures and short setae; mediolongitudinal sulcus thin and not obvious, both sides with a shallow depression; pronotal groove thin but obvious basally, absent in middle of anterior part, thin but deep at lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021165FCE8FA68FCD2" box="[1333,1422,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Prosternum distinctly raised before procoxae, surface wrinkled with sparse short setae; apex of prosternal process rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FC04FF1EFB9E" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Elytra long ovoid, more than 1.5× longer than wide in dorsal view, humerus strongly narrowed, widest at apical 1/3, disc with regular rows of strong foveolate punctures; scutellum transverse, nearly triangular; wings completely reduced.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FBB0FE8CFB65" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Metaventrite and abdomen finely covered with short thin setae and dense small punctures; median sulcus distinct, extending from anterior margin to ca. 2/3 of metaventrite length. Abdominal ventrite I longest, shorter than combined lengths of ventrites III and IV, wrinkled basally; ventrite II slightly longer than metaventrite III; metaventrites III and IV distinctly concave; ventrite V slightly shorter than combined lengths of ventrites III and IV, apex rounded; apical margin of abdominal ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021740FB00FC81FB4A" box="[784,871,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) medially impressed, posterior and lateral margins bearing long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FB5FFE59FAF5" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Femora claviform medially, strongly expanded in distal halves; all tibiae covered with brown setae apically; pro- and mesotibiae slightly curved, metatibia straight; tarsomeres simple, apical pro- and mesotarsomeres shorter than combined lengths of proximal four tarsomeres, apical metatarsomere shorter than combined lengths of proximal three metatarsomeres.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FA28FD60FA4E" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021517FA28FE22FA12" box="[327,452,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Figs 3F–H</figureCitation>
) symmetrical in dorsal view, distinctly curved in profile; spiculum gastrale (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA1602116CFA28FA72FA12" box="[1340,1428,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, short, with large apical lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FA67FA93FA69" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1397,1483,1510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Measurements: BL 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA160215F3FA60FDEFFA69" box="[419,521,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.66" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="16.6">16.6 mm</quantity>
