<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA16021610FA60FD7EFA69" box="[576,664,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA16021689FA60FCD7FA69" box="[729,817,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
, PL 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA16021733FA60FC5DFA69" box="[867,955,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA160217A7FA60FBA9FA69" box="[1015,1103,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
, EL 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA160210D3FA60FB3DFA69" box="[1155,1243,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="9.4">9.4 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="532C55CEFFFA16021148FA60FA97FA69" box="[1304,1393,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497FA44FE24F9DD" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
Female (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA16021579FA44FE67F986" box="[297,385,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,356,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-112@2.[151,1436,345,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. H. (H.) ferreri sp. nov., female; B. H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., male; C. Same, female; D. H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., male; E. Same, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598175/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
): Similar to male. Posterior margin of ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA1602179FFA44FBFDF986" box="[975,1051,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
) rounded and covered with sparse long setae. Spiculum (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA160215C3F9B8FE39F9A2" box="[403,479,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
) nearly straight, apex rounded and slightly dilated. Apex of ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA1602115BF9B8FABCF9A2" box="[1291,1370,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[174,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1437,181,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598180" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598180/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3J</figureCitation>
) with a long and two short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497F9F7FA93F9F9" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1397,1627,1654]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
