</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFFA16021497F9D4FF16F8A6" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497F9D4FF16F8A6" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021497F9D4FE36F916" bold="true" box="[199,464,1663,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
In general habitus the new species most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFFA1602102BF92BFEC6F932" authority="Fairmaire, 1891" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis" subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA1602102BF92BFB71F916" box="[1147,1175,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA160210F9F92BFB22F916" box="[1193,1220,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021086F9D4FABBF916" box="[1238,1373,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">sculpticollis</emphasis>
Fairmaire, 1891
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="561036C9FFFA1602153CF908FE35F932" box="[364,467,1699,1725]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, with both species having a long-oval body and a pronotum with a pair of shallow impressions. However, 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFFA160215F2F963FD55F96E" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhou &amp; Liu &amp; Huang &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhou &amp; Liu &amp; Huang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[418,691,1735,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tianbaoyanensis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA160215F2F963FE58F96E" box="[418,446,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021580F963FE0DF96E" box="[464,491,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA160215ADF96CFD55F96E" box="[509,691,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">tianbaoyanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA160216ECF96CFCF1F96E" bold="true" box="[700,791,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BD939942FFFA160216ECF96CFCF1F96E" box="[700,791,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be separated from the latter species by the different form of the aedeagus: lateral margin of lobes are straight in 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFFA1602176DF947FBFBF88A" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1891" box="[829,1053,1771,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis" subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA1602176DF947FCBFF88A" box="[829,857,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA1602173AF947FC60F88A" box="[874,902,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA160217C6F940FBFBF88A" box="[918,1053,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">sculpticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while distinctly wavy in the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFFA16021497F898FDEEF8C2" box="[199,520,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497F898FDEEF8C2" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,520,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021497F898FE87F8C2" bold="true" box="[199,353,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="ECC3B8BBFFFA16021537F898FE48F8C2" box="[359,430,1843,1869]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="561036C9FFFA160215E9F898FDE2F8C2" box="[441,516,1843,1869]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Fujian</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFFA16021497F8FCFD90F819" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497F8FCFD90F819" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021497F8FCFEC1F8FE" bold="true" box="[199,295,1879,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Biology.</emphasis>
Adults of this species were collected on tree trunks at night, while during the day they are hidden under tree bark and difficult to find (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFA160215BAF8D0FD8CF819" box="[490,618,1915,1942]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,785,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-228@7.[151,1435,705,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitats of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. General environment of type locality of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov.; B. Live individuals of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov. photographed in nature; C. Live individuals of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598184/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Figs 5A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFFA16021497F834FE12F852" pageId="4" pageNumber="596" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFA16021497F834FE12F852" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFA16021497F834FEA8F836" bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the 
<typeStatus id="4B6F4689FFFA16021681F80BFCE7F835" box="[721,769,1952,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="596">type</typeStatus>
